13.*** A man has nine children born at regular intervals.  The sum of  the
square of their ages is equal to the square of his own age.  What are  the
ages of the children?

14.**  A  man is walking his dog on the lead towards home at  a  steady  3
MPH.   When they are 7 miles from home,  the man lets his dog off  of  the
lead.  The dog immediately runs off towards home at 8 MPH.  When  the  dog
reaches  the house it turns around and runs back to the man  at  the  same
speed.   When  it reaches the man it turns back for the  house.   This  is
repeated until the man gets home and lets in the dog.  How many miles does
the dog cover from being let off of the lead to being let into the house?

